data.enText: to event/situation
what you do, say or think as a result of sth that has happened
What was his reaction to the news?

data.chText: 我当即的反应是大吃一惊。
data.enText: My immediate reaction was one of shock.

data.chText: 一位发言人说，这些变动不是针对公司最近的损失而作出的反应。
data.enText: A spokesman said the changes were not in reaction to the company's recent losses.

data.chText: 对她获任命为主管一事，人们的反应褒贬不一。
data.enText: There has been a mixed reaction to her appointment as director.

data.chText: 这个决定引起了当地居民的愤怒抗议。
data.enText: The decision provoked an angry reaction from local residents.

data.chText: 我试着摇了摇他，但他一动不动。
data.enText: I tried shaking him but there was no reaction.
change in attitudes
a change in people's attitudes or behaviour caused by disapproval of the attitudes, etc. of the past

data.chText: 传统家庭价值观的恢复是对近几十年来放纵自由的一种抗拒。
data.enText: The return to traditional family values is a reaction against the permissiveness of recent decades.
to drugs
a response by the body, usually a bad one, to a drug, chemical substance, etc.
to have an allergic reaction to a drug
to danger
the ability to move quickly in response to sth, especially if in danger
a skilled driver with quick reactions
against progress
opposition to social or political progress or change

data.chText: 反动势力使得改革举步维艰。
data.enText: The forces of reaction made change difficult.
science
a chemical change produced by two or more substances acting on each other
a chemical/nuclear reaction
a force shown by sth in response to another force, which is of equal strength and acts in the opposite direction

simple_means.memory_skill: re 相反；反对；不 + action 行动 → 反动；反应

ex.chText: 该评论员批评了政府对石油危机的反应。
ex.enText: The commentator criticized the government's reaction to the oil crisis.

ex.chText: 这一政策引起了工人们的愤怒。
ex.enText: The policy produced an angry reaction from workers.

synonyms.bx: 指对发生的事情或他人的话语所作的反应，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 请尽量给每个作品提点反馈意见。
ex.enText: Please try to give each piece of work some feedback.

ex.chText: 他们对我的工作提出了一些意见。
ex.enText: They gave me some feedback on my work.

synonyms.bx: 指针对某事物给出的建议、批评等，常后接介词 on。

ex.chText: 她敲了敲门，但是没人应声。
ex.enText: She knocked on the door, but there was no reply.

ex.chText: 他们的信还没有收到任何回复。
ex.enText: No reply to their letter has been received.

synonyms.bx: 指通过言语、信件等对某事作的回应，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 她儿子没有回答，继续看电影。
ex.enText: Her son made no response, and went on with his movie.

ex.chText: 我现写信回复您的询问。
ex.enText: I am writing in response to your inquiry.

ex.chText: 这部小说得到读者的好评。
ex.enText: This novel has received a positive response from readers.

synonyms.bx: 指口头或书面的答复，也指对某事的反应，常后接介词 to。

tr: doing something in opposition to another way of doing it that you don't like
example: his style of painting was a reaction against cubism

tr: a bodily process occurring due to the effect of some antecedent stimulus or agent
example: a bad reaction to the medicine
his responses have slowed with age

tr: an idea evoked by some experience
example: his reaction to the news was to start planning what to do

tr: extreme conservatism in political or social matters
example: the forces of reaction carried the election

tr: a response that reveals a person's feelings or attitude
example: he was pleased by the audience's reaction to his performance
John feared his mother's reaction when she saw the broken lamp

tr: (mechanics) the equal and opposite force that is produced when any force is applied to a body
example: every action has an equal and opposite reaction

tr: (chemistry) a process in which one or more substances are changed into others
example: there was a chemical reaction of the lime with the ground water

value.def: Your reaction to something that has happened or something that you have experienced is what you feel, say, or do because of it.

example.ex: Reaction to the visit is mixed...
example.tran: 对这次访问的反应不一。

example.ex: The initial reaction of most participants is fear...
example.tran: 多数参与者的最初反应是恐惧。

example.ex: He was surprised that his answer should have caused such a strong reaction.
example.tran: 他很惊讶自己的回答会引起如此强烈的反响。

value.def: A reaction against something is a way of behaving or doing something that is deliberately different from what has been done before.

example.ex: All new fashion starts out as a reaction against existing convention...
example.tran: 所有新时尚都是从打破现有常规开始的。

example.ex: Her three years of freedom seemed like a reaction against that childhood.
example.tran: 她那3年的自由仿佛是对孩童时代的反叛。

value.def: If there is a reaction against something, it becomes unpopular.

example.ex: Premature moves in this respect might well provoke a reaction against the reform...
example.tran: 在这方面不成熟的举动很可能引发对改革的抵触情绪。

example.ex: The government response seems to be the result of strong public reaction against the police apathy.
example.tran: 政府的回应似乎是公众强烈抵制警察冷漠执法的结果。

value.def: Your reactions are your ability to move quickly in response to something, for example when you are in danger.

example.ex: If his reactions are so slow, he shouldn't be in charge of a bus...
example.tran: 如果他的反应太慢，就不应该开公交汽车。

example.ex: The sport requires very fast reactions.
example.tran: 这项运动要求极快的反应力。

value.def: Reaction is the belief that the political or social system of your country should not change.

example.ex: Thus, he aided reaction and thwarted progress.
example.tran: 因此，他帮助反动派阻挠进步。

example.ex: ...their victory against the forces of reaction and censorship.
example.tran: 他们取得的对保守势力和审查制度的胜利

value.def: A chemical reaction is a process in which two substances combine together chemically to form another substance.

example.ex: Ozone is produced by the reaction between oxygen and ultraviolet light...
example.tran: 臭氧由氧气和紫外线发生反应而产生。

example.ex: Catalysts are materials which greatly speed up chemical reactions.
example.tran: 催化剂是可以大大加速化学反应的物质。

value.def: If you have a reaction to a substance such as a drug, or to something you have touched, you are affected unpleasantly or made ill by it.

example.ex: Every year, 5000 people have life-threatening reactions to anaesthetics...
example.tran: 每年有5,000人对麻醉剂产生致命反应。

example.ex: Common foods which cause this kind of reaction are fish, eggs, and shellfish.
example.tran: 引发这种不良反应的常见食物包括鱼、蛋和贝类。
